1
00:00:04,042 --> 00:00:07,627
Prabhupād once said, when people
would say, “Oh, your disciples …

2
00:00:07,627 --> 00:00:12,221
bunch of fanatics, and they just say
so many offensive things to people.”

3
00:00:12,221 --> 00:00:15,167
—and I’m here 
to say that’s true—

4
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:22,253
I’ve done that so many times,
hopefully less as time goes on—

5
00:00:22,253 --> 00:00:26,169
but Prabhupād said, “Oh, please,
what they have is so valuable,

6
00:00:26,169 --> 00:00:32,002
they’re so protective of it, so don’t mind it, 
please forgive them.”

7
00:00:32,002 --> 00:00:35,700
That was his way 
of dealing with it.

8
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:42,614
The first time I went to India,
Prabhupād got our visas for us.

9
00:00:42,614 --> 00:00:45,456
Is he more affectionate than a father?

10
00:00:45,456 --> 00:00:47,544
He got our visas.

11
00:00:47,544 --> 00:00:51,138
He goes to an Indian embassy
and got visas for thirty devotees.

12
00:00:51,138 --> 00:00:54,337
I was part of that group.

13
00:00:54,337 --> 00:00:59,253
And while there, he blasted
the Indian ambassador.

14
00:00:59,253 --> 00:01:01,502
Just blasted him!
[Laughing]

15
00:01:01,502 --> 00:01:07,251
And then he came out,
and he’d never had a ‘7 Up’ before

16
00:01:07,251 --> 00:01:10,503
and he was thirsty,
and this is in New York.

17
00:01:10,503 --> 00:01:15,489
There’s some guy, like, selling pretzels
on the street … Italian ices, 7 Up …

18
00:01:15,489 --> 00:01:17,752
and Prabhupād says,
“Do they have Limca?”

19
00:01:17,752 --> 00:01:19,667
And they go, “No, Prabhupād,
they don’t have Limca,

20
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:23,918
but there’s this other drink called 7 Up”
and they gave it to him,

21
00:01:23,918 --> 00:01:26,712
and Prabhupād’s drinking it,
pouring it into his mouth,

22
00:01:26,712 --> 00:01:31,241
and he goes, “Do you think
that I spoke too strongly?”

23
00:01:31,241 --> 00:01:34,920
And everyone’s, “Oh no, Prabhupād!
What you said …”

24
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:38,642
You know …
[Laughing]

25
00:01:38,642 --> 00:01:42,975
But everyone was thinking,
“God, did he blast that guy!”

26
00:01:42,975 --> 00:01:44,752
“No, Prabhupād!”

27
00:01:44,752 --> 00:01:48,085
And Prabhupād said,
“Yes, it was strong.”

28
00:01:48,085 --> 00:01:50,252
He said, 
“I can do that,
 
 

29
00:01:50,252 --> 00:01:52,168
I’m an old man,
they will take it from me,

30
00:01:52,168 --> 00:01:54,168
because if you do that,
they will beat you!”

31
00:01:54,168 --> 00:01:57,446
Because he knew, whatever he did,
we’re gonna imitate that.

32
00:01:57,446 --> 00:02:01,201
Then, we thirty, we’re gonna march in
and blast the Indian ambassador,

33
00:02:01,201 --> 00:02:03,951
because we’re disciples
of Prabhupād.

34
00:02:03,951 --> 00:02:10,715
So he’s cautioning us 
not to imitate him.

35
00:02:10,715 --> 00:02:15,669
But he wanted that like
we would go to India,

36
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:19,503
and he said, “They may think
you’re like dancing white elephants,

37
00:02:19,503 --> 00:02:25,085
but they’ll all come to see
the dance of the white elephants.”

38
00:02:25,085 --> 00:02:31,168
Janārdan Mahārāj was there
and so many others, Sāgar Mahārāj,

39
00:02:31,168 --> 00:02:35,752
and the people, 
they would listen from us.

40
00:02:35,752 --> 00:02:37,611
They’re going away 
from their culture,

41
00:02:37,611 --> 00:02:43,618
but seeing these young middle-class
aristocratic white kids from America,

42
00:02:43,618 --> 00:02:45,286
they’re taking 
to Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

43
00:02:45,286 --> 00:02:49,161
Then they think,
“We’d better to look at it again.”

